    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>As Allies and Iraqis Face the Ravages of War</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael and Martha Gardner letter thanks readers for support for their son Michael, who is serving in Iraq; drawing (Mar 25 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Watching, and Praying, as a Son's Fate Unfolds'' (news article, March 25):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Watching, and Praying, as a Son's Fate Unfolds'' (news article, March 25):</p>
        <p>We want to express our gratitude to several New York families that called us after reading your article to express their appreciation and support for our son, Cpl. Michael P. Gardner II, a marine serving in Iraq.</p>
        <p>We are grateful for their encouragement.</p>
        <p>Sept. 11 proved that New York is the greatest city in the world, and now the men and women in our military will enable us to show the world that the United States is the greatest country.</p>
        <p>MARTHA GARDNER  MICHAEL GARDNER  Hunt Valley, Md., March 27, 2003</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
